column5: Dropped by for a look see this morning.  all froze up nicely , ramp is accesible and vehicles are travelling out to the whitefish grounds , Bit slippery so cleats would help.  Not good for sleds due to 0 snow coverage.     Did speak with one returning fisherman , who claimed 14" of ice straight out ion 80 feet of water. No info on the bite.
Big change from yesterday!  Lot at ramp was full of vehicles so we can expect a big crowd tomorrow.  TB
Should have looked through the post B4 I posted.  See you in the AM
there will be 500 plus trucks and cars this coming weekend with conditions and posts like this............

saw the same conditions     <embed width="448" height="361" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="transparent" src="http://i25.photobucket.com/player.swf?file=http://vid25.photobucket.com/albums/c52/Mrbeee1954/DIGI0001.flv">
Ya beat me to it, I was there a little after 11am looking around...  maureen
You prefishing son of a gun.Hope it dont snow and cover up that red X you put out there.  See ya all in the AM,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Hope tonights event, dosent make us late.

So guys were there cars or 4x4's driving on the ice? I am asking as I am wondering should I come with the car or with the SUV? Seems like all slush and snow are gone/frozen and we should still have plenty of ice...  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
cars trucks and vans were out there
Bring the 4x4. Im going to wear my Sunday best shoes so I can bumpper shag behind ya icefishermen. That was so cool to do,,,,,,,,,,,,,back then.LOL
Thanks Terry. And no one getting stuck? Man you just won the price for the quickest reply ha ha ha ;-) I may see you on the ice in the next few days Bud!  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
I could do it Bud...but it'll be nice if I can avoid it as it'll burn tripple the amount of gas my car uses.  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
the water and slush seems to be frozen and there is no real snow, so nothing to get stuck on  I saw a lot of  vehicles out there, for a friday an awful lot of them hope to see you on the weekend
Terry,I,ll be sure to bring my screwdriver and vise grips.Just incase.Oh will I need to bring a file too? BWAHAHAHAHA
Hey Hey I am always prepared oh and I am bring this I keep it in then freezer
That looks like the same trout that had the Loblaw's bar code on it...
